THE ART OF ARIAN

ARIAN's latest work, Mithraion (Μιθραίον) (2024) is a Total Work of Art (TWoA) [Teilkunstwerk/Gesamtkunstwerk], spanning an array of artforms including yet not limited to drawing, painting, literature, music; computer, performance and land art—in tandem with non-artforms such as essays, fieldwork, monographs and mythographies. A work of Lived Literature (LL) and best thought of as a book, yet conceived as modular media, Mithraion is concerned with time.

COLLECT THE FIRST CHAPTER FOLLOW ON SOCIAL MEDIA

ARIAN is an artist and author. ARIAN's works have been presented at and catalogued by, among others, the Royal Anthropological Institute (RAI), Ars Electronica, Miami Art Week, Max Planck Institute for Empirical Aesthetics, and the Royal Musical Association (RMA). ARIAN has exhibited in New York, London, Miami, Zürich, Barcelona, among others, and is published by MIT Press and Cambridge University Press, respectively. ARIAN’s research is located at the interface of anthropologies of science and religion—with key contributions to visual culture, dramaturgy and theory of art.
